note.body:
Okay:
* for the "only one event imported" - that was due to a stupid first class bug in the code, flipped condition to recognize whether the previous create worked or not;

* for the timezone - as the event has no time zone set for the DTSTART, the m365 calendar defaults to UTC. I changed it to use the user-configured time zone instead, which is the floating time about after all. The gnome-calendar surely used the system time zone to "fill the time zone".
